[2026-03-12T15:46:39Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M5zerrENuK39Cn9Y311Bzn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me provide a detailed report to the user.\n\n## Summary Report: Host Orchestration Loop Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough examination of the Cloche codebase, here's a comprehensive analysis of the host orchestration system:\n\n### 1. **Host Orchestration Loop Overview**\n\nThe orchestration loop is implemented in `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`. It manages continuous execution of host workflows for a project, keeping up to `MaxConcurrent` runs active. There are two operational modes:\n\n- **Three-Phase Mode** (`NewPhaseLoop`): Uses distinct list-tasks, main, and finalize workflows\n- **Legacy Mode** (`NewLoop`): Single-function execution model\n\n### 2. **How List-Tasks Results Are Processed**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`, lines 174-271 (`runPhased()` method)\n\nThe three-phase orchestration loop processes list-tasks results as follows:\n\n1. **List-tasks Execution** (`pickTaskFromPhase()`, lines 309-351):\n   - Calls `l.listTasks(ctx, projectDir)` to fetch available tasks\n   - Returns `[]Task` with fields: `ID`, `Status`, `Title`, `Description`, `Metadata`\n   - Tasks are cached in `l.lastTasks` for snapshot queries\n   - Empty tasks or error returns `(\"\", false)` to skip launching\n\n2. **Task Filtering**:\n   - Only tasks where `task.IsOpen()` are eligible (status must be \"open\" or empty string)\n   - **File:** `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`, lines 30-32\n   - Closed and in-progress tasks are automatically skipped\n\n3. **Deduplication**:\n   - Tracks assigned tasks in `l.dedup` map (task ID → assignment time)\n   - Expires entries older than `DedupTimeout` (default 5 minutes)\n   - Prevents the same task from being assigned within the timeout window\n   - Re-assignment happens only after timeout expires\n\n4. **Run Creation Flow**:\n   - Once a task is picked, it's removed from the dedup check\n   - `mainFn` is called in a goroutine with the task ID\n   - After main completes, `finalizeFn` is called (if configured)\n   - Both phases receive `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable\n\n### 3. **Run Record Creation During Orchestration**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, lines 82-90\n\nWhen a host workflow run executes:\n\n```\n1. Create Run Record: domain.NewRun(orchRunID, wf.Name)\n2. Set Metadata:\n   - ProjectDir: the project directory\n   - IsHost: true (marks as host run)\n   - Title: optional one-line summary\n3. CreateRun(ctx, hostRun) persists to store\n4. hostRun.Start() sets State to RunStateRunning\n5. UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun) persists the state change\n6. Execute workflow steps via Engine\n7. Final UpdateRun with terminal state (succeeded/failed)\n```\n\n**Key Fields Set:**\n- `ID`: Generated unique run ID (format: `<workflow>-<timestamp>`)\n- `WorkflowName`: Name of executed workflow (e.g., \"main\")\n- `State`: Initial state is `RunStatePending`\n- `ProjectDir`: Project location\n- `IsHost`: Boolean flag distinguishing host vs container runs\n- `ParentRunID`: Set when child runs are dispatched via container workflow steps\n- `BaseSHA`: Git HEAD SHA at run start (for result branch creation)\n\n### 4. **RunStore Interface and Persistence**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`, lines 10-19\n\nThe `RunStore` interface provides:\n\n```go\nCreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\nGetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\nUpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\nDeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\nListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\nListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\nListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\nListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**SQLite Implementation:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n- **Schema:** `runs` table stores core run data (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id)\n- **Active Run Count:** `countActiveHostRuns()` in loop.go queries runs where `IsHost=true` AND `State IN ('pending', 'running')`\n- **Persistence:** All run state changes trigger `UpdateRun()` calls to maintain consistency\n\n### 5. **Run Status Types and Constants**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, lines 8-16\n\nOnly five status states exist (NO hidden or skip statuses):\n\n```go\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\nThere are **no \"hidden\" or \"skip\" status values** for runs. Tasks (not runs) have a `Status` field that can be \"open\", \"closed\", or \"in-progress\", but this affects task selection, not run status.\n\n### 6. **Orchestration Loop Control Flow**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 870-921 (Three-Phase Setup)\n\nThe EnableLoop RPC creates an orchestration loop:\n\n1. **List-Tasks Phase:**\n   - Runs the \"list-tasks\" workflow from host.cloche\n   - Parses output as JSONL (one Task JSON per line)\n   - **File:** `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`, lines 72-89 (`ParseTasksJSONL`)\n\n2. **Main Phase:**\n   - Receives task ID from list-tasks\n   - Runs \"main\" workflow with `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n   - Returns `RunResult` with RunID and State\n   - Tracks assignment in `taskRuns` map\n\n3. **Finalize Phase:**\n   - Runs \"finalize\" workflow after main completes\n   - Receives outcome as `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` env var\n   - Runs on both success and failure\n\n### 7. **Key Data Structures**\n\n**Task Assignment Tracking:**\n```go\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string  // run ID handling this task (set after main completes)\n}\n\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n    Task       Task\n    Assigned   bool\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string  // empty if not yet known\n}\n```\n\n**Run Snapshot:** `GetTaskSnapshot()` returns current pipeline state with assignment info\n\n### 8. **Active Run Counting**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`, lines 485-498\n\nCapacity management via:\n```go\nactive := l.countActiveHostRuns()\nif active >= l.config.MaxConcurrent {\n    break  // Don't launch more runs\n}\n```\n\nQueries only host runs: `r.IsHost && (r.State == RunStatePending || r.State == RunStateRunning)`\n\n### Key Files Referenced\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Run execution and persistence\n3. `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - Task definition and parsing\n4. `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Step execution for host workflows\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run domain model and states\n6. `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface\n7. `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite persistence\n8. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - Loop creation and management"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a08e099bd35191e43 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65291\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 58341</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88adcd43-a2b6-4c68-8f0c-4f6b9fedf8a8","uuid":"aefcdf05-1488-4504-8148-dd417dcd8b5e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how the host orchestration loop works, specifically:\n\n1. How list-tasks results are processed in the host workflow executor\n2. How run records are created during orchestration\n3. The RunStore interface and how runs are persisted\n4. Any existing \"skip\" or \"hidden\" status for runs\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- Host workflow executor code (internal/host/)\n- Run creation logic during orchestration\n- list-tasks related code\n- RunStore interface and implementations\n- Run status types/constants\n- The orchestration loop that processes list-tasks results and creates runs\n\nRead all relevant files in full. Be very thorough - check internal/domain/, internal/ports/, internal/adapters/, internal/host/, and cmd/ directories.","agentId":"a08e099bd35191e43","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me provide a detailed report to the user.\n\n## Summary Report: Host Orchestration Loop Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough examination of the Cloche codebase, here's a comprehensive analysis of the host orchestration system:\n\n### 1. **Host Orchestration Loop Overview**\n\nThe orchestration loop is implemented in `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`. It manages continuous execution of host workflows for a project, keeping up to `MaxConcurrent` runs active. There are two operational modes:\n\n- **Three-Phase Mode** (`NewPhaseLoop`): Uses distinct list-tasks, main, and finalize workflows\n- **Legacy Mode** (`NewLoop`): Single-function execution model\n\n### 2. **How List-Tasks Results Are Processed**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`, lines 174-271 (`runPhased()` method)\n\nThe three-phase orchestration loop processes list-tasks results as follows:\n\n1. **List-tasks Execution** (`pickTaskFromPhase()`, lines 309-351):\n   - Calls `l.listTasks(ctx, projectDir)` to fetch available tasks\n   - Returns `[]Task` with fields: `ID`, `Status`, `Title`, `Description`, `Metadata`\n   - Tasks are cached in `l.lastTasks` for snapshot queries\n   - Empty tasks or error returns `(\"\", false)` to skip launching\n\n2. **Task Filtering**:\n   - Only tasks where `task.IsOpen()` are eligible (status must be \"open\" or empty string)\n   - **File:** `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`, lines 30-32\n   - Closed and in-progress tasks are automatically skipped\n\n3. **Deduplication**:\n   - Tracks assigned tasks in `l.dedup` map (task ID → assignment time)\n   - Expires entries older than `DedupTimeout` (default 5 minutes)\n   - Prevents the same task from being assigned within the timeout window\n   - Re-assignment happens only after timeout expires\n\n4. **Run Creation Flow**:\n   - Once a task is picked, it's removed from the dedup check\n   - `mainFn` is called in a goroutine with the task ID\n   - After main completes, `finalizeFn` is called (if configured)\n   - Both phases receive `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable\n\n### 3. **Run Record Creation During Orchestration**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, lines 82-90\n\nWhen a host workflow run executes:\n\n```\n1. Create Run Record: domain.NewRun(orchRunID, wf.Name)\n2. Set Metadata:\n   - ProjectDir: the project directory\n   - IsHost: true (marks as host run)\n   - Title: optional one-line summary\n3. CreateRun(ctx, hostRun) persists to store\n4. hostRun.Start() sets State to RunStateRunning\n5. UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun) persists the state change\n6. Execute workflow steps via Engine\n7. Final UpdateRun with terminal state (succeeded/failed)\n```\n\n**Key Fields Set:**\n- `ID`: Generated unique run ID (format: `<workflow>-<timestamp>`)\n- `WorkflowName`: Name of executed workflow (e.g., \"main\")\n- `State`: Initial state is `RunStatePending`\n- `ProjectDir`: Project location\n- `IsHost`: Boolean flag distinguishing host vs container runs\n- `ParentRunID`: Set when child runs are dispatched via container workflow steps\n- `BaseSHA`: Git HEAD SHA at run start (for result branch creation)\n\n### 4. **RunStore Interface and Persistence**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`, lines 10-19\n\nThe `RunStore` interface provides:\n\n```go\nCreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\nGetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\nUpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\nDeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\nListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\nListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\nListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\nListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**SQLite Implementation:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n- **Schema:** `runs` table stores core run data (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title, is_host, parent_run_id)\n- **Active Run Count:** `countActiveHostRuns()` in loop.go queries runs where `IsHost=true` AND `State IN ('pending', 'running')`\n- **Persistence:** All run state changes trigger `UpdateRun()` calls to maintain consistency\n\n### 5. **Run Status Types and Constants**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, lines 8-16\n\nOnly five status states exist (NO hidden or skip statuses):\n\n```go\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\nThere are **no \"hidden\" or \"skip\" status values** for runs. Tasks (not runs) have a `Status` field that can be \"open\", \"closed\", or \"in-progress\", but this affects task selection, not run status.\n\n### 6. **Orchestration Loop Control Flow**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 870-921 (Three-Phase Setup)\n\nThe EnableLoop RPC creates an orchestration loop:\n\n1. **List-Tasks Phase:**\n   - Runs the \"list-tasks\" workflow from host.cloche\n   - Parses output as JSONL (one Task JSON per line)\n   - **File:** `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`, lines 72-89 (`ParseTasksJSONL`)\n\n2. **Main Phase:**\n   - Receives task ID from list-tasks\n   - Runs \"main\" workflow with `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n   - Returns `RunResult` with RunID and State\n   - Tracks assignment in `taskRuns` map\n\n3. **Finalize Phase:**\n   - Runs \"finalize\" workflow after main completes\n   - Receives outcome as `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` env var\n   - Runs on both success and failure\n\n### 7. **Key Data Structures**\n\n**Task Assignment Tracking:**\n```go\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string  // run ID handling this task (set after main completes)\n}\n\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n    Task       Task\n    Assigned   bool\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string  // empty if not yet known\n}\n```\n\n**Run Snapshot:** `GetTaskSnapshot()` returns current pipeline state with assignment info\n\n### 8. **Active Run Counting**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`, lines 485-498\n\nCapacity management via:\n```go\nactive := l.countActiveHostRuns()\nif active >= l.config.MaxConcurrent {\n    break  // Don't launch more runs\n}\n```\n\nQueries only host runs: `r.IsHost && (r.State == RunStatePending || r.State == RunStateRunning)`\n\n### Key Files Referenced\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Run execution and persistence\n3. `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - Task definition and parsing\n4. `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Step execution for host workflows\n5. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run domain model and states\n6. `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface\n7. `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite persistence\n8. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - Loop creation and management"}],"totalDurationMs":58341,"totalTokens":65291,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2381,"cache_read_input_tokens":60869,"output_tokens":2041,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2381},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
